{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ae754abb-09c8-4128-8ed3-6eee9702e4cb","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.XUnit` instead.\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly via the built executable (MTP produces a self-contained test host).\n\n**Key notes:**\n- If you stay on **xUnit v2.9.x**, use the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.XUnit` bridge package — it adapts v2 tests to MTP.\n- If you're ready to upgrade to **xUnit v3**, swap `xunit` for `xunit.v3` and use `xunit.v3.runner.mtp`.\n- Remove any `<GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>` or `<EnableMSTestRunner>` properties that don't apply to xUnit.\n\nWhich route (stay on v2 or upgrade to v3) fits your situation?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"10030bcc-c807-41f5-8baf-3d9b0fca4936","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":396,"requestId":"67E4:2636C7:2ABECB5:2EFDD66:69FD337C"},"id":"00e2b12e-e966-4334-b922-09fce3c78e58","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:51:18.221Z","parentId":"fb45af9c-dccd-49e3-891b-578d145f64a3"}
